# XAMPP Stack Environment Rules

## Environment Context
- OS: Windows/Mac (XAMPP Environment)
- Local Server Path: Typically inside htdocs folder
- PHP Version: Standard XAMPP PHP (Check errors via PHP Error Logs or display_errors)
- Database: MySQL / MariaDB (Default port 3306)

## PHP & SQL Coding Standards
- ALWAYS use PHP Data Objects (PDO) for database connections to ensure security.
- ALWAYS use prepared statements with named parameters to prevent SQL injection.
- Do not use deprecated `mysql_*` or procedural `mysqli_*` functions unless explicitly asked.
- Wrap database transactions in try-catch blocks and log exceptions.
- Ensure all HTML forms include basic CSRF protection tokens handled via PHP sessions.

## Workflow & System Commands
- If a script requires testing, you may use curl commands in the terminal targeting `http://localhost/YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER_NAME/` if XAMPP Apache is running.
- Do not attempt to restart the Apache or MySQL services via terminal commands, as XAMPP handles this via its Control Panel.
- Always check for the existence of database configuration files (like `db.php` or `config.php`) before generating new connection code.
